  "difficultyLevel": 5,
  "lyrics": "Sometimes the dark hits you right in the heart and you can't feel anything but your heart And all night you dumped the thoughts of light and fright on me and I can't take it no more Because who should just be you? Who should just hear you? Who should just be clearer than the thing that you cleared through? Because experience rots your mind and you find that you're just like every other one of us With your feelings that encapsulates the mind that you feel Can't you understand locally and breathe in your own? Can't you be you? Just be you And don't be for the thought of the judgment of the crew To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture You of life To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture You of your own life Sometimes I think you don't know who you are I'm here to tell you more than you think It's like a piece of a whole which I have so sprinkled over the galaxy and the stars The wrongs and the lights, you find your place there and you don't find it To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture of us I know there's a better way I know you'll find that brighter day As for me, I gotta hop the road over there Find my start and be better from my heart And I'm gonna do it for me and I'll be me Can you be you and we'll find happiness somewhere else again? That's just the way it goes, I'm sorry It's time to be free then It's time to be us again Be all you can be",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 25.860000610351562,
      "text": "Sometimes the dark hits you right in the heart and you can't feel anything but your heart",
      "start": 17.940000534057617
    },
    {
      "end": 35.15999984741211,
      "text": "And all night you dumped the thoughts of light and fright on me and I can't take it no more",
      "start": 28.100000381469727
    },
    {
      "end": 39.81999969482422,
      "text": "Because who should just be you? Who should just hear you?",
      "start": 35.20000076293945
    },
    {
      "end": 44.70000076293945,
      "text": "Who should just be clearer than the thing that you cleared through?",
      "start": 40.41999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 53.08000183105469,
      "text": "Because experience rots your mind and you find that you're just like every other one of us",
      "start": 45.2400016784668
    },
    {
      "end": 57.7599983215332,
      "text": "With your feelings that encapsulates the mind that you feel",
      "start": 53.08000183105469
    },
    {
      "end": 62.84000015258789,
      "text": "Can't you understand locally and breathe in your own?",
      "start": 57.7599983215332
    },
    {
      "end": 67,
      "text": "Can't you be you? Just be you",
      "start": 63.400001525878906
    },
    {
      "end": 71.94000244140625,
      "text": "And don't be for the thought of the judgment of the crew",
      "start": 67
    },
    {
      "end": 76.9800033569336,
      "text": "To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture",
      "start": 72.0199966430664
    },
    {
      "end": 80.27999877929688,
      "text": "You of life",
      "start": 77.76000213623047
    },
    {
      "end": 85.72000122070312,
      "text": "To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture",
      "start": 80.27999877929688
    },
    {
      "end": 88.27999877929688,
      "text": "You of your own life",
      "start": 85.72000122070312
    },
    {
      "end": 94.4800033569336,
      "text": "Sometimes I think you don't know who you are",
      "start": 89.5
    },
    {
      "end": 101.86000061035156,
      "text": "I'm here to tell you more than you think",
      "start": 98.04000091552734
    },
    {
      "end": 108.62000274658203,
      "text": "It's like a piece of a whole which I have so sprinkled over the galaxy and the stars",
      "start": 101.86000061035156
    },
    {
      "end": 115.62000274658203,
      "text": "The wrongs and the lights, you find your place there and you don't find it",
      "start": 108.62000274658203
    },
    {
      "end": 125.0199966430664,
      "text": "To me all you can be is a lie and there's a fracture of us",
      "start": 116.16000366210938
    },
    {
      "end": 129.39999389648438,
      "text": "I know there's a better way",
      "start": 125.0199966430664
    },
    {
      "end": 134.9600067138672,
      "text": "I know you'll find that brighter day",
      "start": 129.55999755859375
    },
    {
      "end": 140.6199951171875,
      "text": "As for me, I gotta hop the road over there",
      "start": 134.9600067138672
    },
    {
      "end": 143.66000366210938,
      "text": "Find my start and be better from my heart",
      "start": 140.6199951171875
    },
    {
      "end": 147.55999755859375,
      "text": "And I'm gonna do it for me and I'll be me",
      "start": 143.66000366210938
    },
    {
      "end": 153.6199951171875,
      "text": "Can you be you and we'll find happiness somewhere else again?",
      "start": 147.55999755859375
    },
    {
      "end": 155.74000549316406,
      "text": "That's just the way it goes, I'm sorry",
      "start": 154.32000732421875
    },
    {
      "end": 158,
      "text": "It's time to be free then",
      "start": 155.94000244140625
    },
    {
      "end": 160.5399932861328,
      "text": "It's time to be us again",
      "start": 158
    },
    {
      "end": 165.5399932861328,
      "text": "Be all you can be",
      "start": 162.27999877929688
    }
  ],
